headlines.shortLinkText: Jaden Ivey injures leg in 4th quarter in Pistons' victory over the Magic

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole scored 30 points to continue his strongest stretch in a Washington uniform as the Wizards beat the Chicago Bulls 125-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole scores 30 as Wizards beat Bulls 125-107

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 32 points, Bam Adebayo flirted with a triple-double and the Miami Heat beat the New Orleans Pelicans 119-108 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro scores 32, Adebayo nears triple-double and Heat never trail in 119-108 win over Pelicans

events.name: Utah Jazz at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 31 points and 21 rebounds, Josh Hart notched his second straight triple-double and the New York Knicks won their ninth straight game, beating the Utah Jazz 119-103 on Wednesday night despite playing <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Hart help Knicks beat Jazz 119-103 without Brunson for their 9th straight win

headlines.description: — Scottie Barnes had 33 points and 13 rebounds and the Toronto Raptors snapped an 11-game losing streak by beating the Brooklyn Nets 130-113 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes scores 33, Quickley has 21 in return as Raptors beat Nets 130-113, snap 11-game slide

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun had 23 points, Jalen Green added 22 and the Houston Rockets built a big lead early in the second half and sailed to a 110-99 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets beat the Mavericks 110-99 to snap a 2-game skid

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 23 points, 17 rebounds and 15 assists in leading the Denver Nuggets to a 139-120 win over Trae Young and the Atlanta Hawks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic has triple-double as Nuggets roll past Hawks 139-120 for 3rd straight win

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox scored 35 points and the Sacramento Kings closed with a 15-0 run to rally past the Philadelphia 76ers 113-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox scores 35 and Kings close with 15-0 surge to rally past 76ers for 113-107 win
